---
---
<section class="bg-white border-b border-[#e5e5e5] px-section" style="padding-left:120px;padding-right:120px;">
  <div class="faq-row border-l border-r border-[#ebebeb] flex items-start">
    <!-- Sticky heading -->
    <div class="faq-sticky flex-1 sticky top-16">
      <div class="px-12 py-[135px]">
        <h2 class="font-heading font-medium text-[#151515] text-[40px] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-1.2px;">Frequently <br />Asked <br />Questions</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- FAQ items -->
    <div class="faq-list-col border-l border-[#e5e5e5] py-[135px]" style="width:799px;">
      <div id="faq-list">
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group" style="margin-bottom:-1px;">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Do I need Salesforce development skills or coding knowledge?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">No. Appnigma is designed for product teams and founders, not Salesforce developers. You describe what you want to build in plain English — Appnigma handles all the technical implementation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group" style="margin-bottom:-1px;">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">How quickly can an integration go live?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">Most customers ship their first managed package within 14 days. Some go live even faster — within a week — depending on the complexity of the integration.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group" style="margin-bottom:-1px;">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Does Appnigma help with getting listed on the AppExchange?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">Yes. Every package Appnigma generates is built to pass Salesforce Security Review and meet AppExchange listing requirements out of the box.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group" style="margin-bottom:-1px;">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Can I deploy across multiple Salesforce orgs?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">Yes. As a managed package, your integration can be installed across unlimited customer orgs — just like any other AppExchange product.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group" style="margin-bottom:-1px;">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Can I update or maintain integrations after deployment?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">Absolutely. You own the generated code and can update or extend your package at any time using Appnigma or directly in the Salesforce dev tools.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group" style="margin-bottom:-1px;">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Is the platform secure / enterprise-ready?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">Yes. Security is core to the product. Every generated artifact follows Salesforce Security Review best practices with 0 PMD violations.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group" style="margin-bottom:-1px;">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">How does this compare to traditional Salesforce consulting?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">Traditional consulting costs $150K+ per year, takes 6+ months, and you don't own the output. Appnigma ships in days, costs a fraction of the price, and you own all the code.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="border-t border-b border-[#ebebeb] group">
          <summary class="bg-[#f9f9f9] flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="font-body font-semibold text-[16px] text-[#151515] leading-[1.1]" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">What kinds of prompts work for building integrations?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4">
              <img src="/assets/675fef3e2fa462d64537ae8e0d580255ba670e73.svg" alt="" class="w-4 h-4" loading="lazy" />
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 py-5 bg-white border-t border-[#ebebeb]">
            <p class="font-body font-normal text-[14px] text-[#525252] leading-[1.5]">Plain English descriptions work best. e.g. "Build a Salesforce managed package that syncs contacts from our app, creates an Opportunity when they upgrade, and shows a Lightning component on the Account page."</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
